{"agent_id":"anon-ab6221f8","agent_seq":8,"timestamp":"2026-06-22T18:29:06.308332073Z","event":{"type":"LabelAdded","issue_uuid":"135aa6c0-bf14-4adc-9bc8-48ef375ebbac","label":"bug"}}
{"agent_id":"anon-ab6221f8","agent_seq":9,"timestamp":"2026-06-22T18:36:53.316100800Z","event":{"type":"CommentAdded","issue_uuid":"135aa6c0-bf14-4adc-9bc8-48ef375ebbac","comment_uuid":"35b8a6e0-c1a6-4179-8522-b6666b6a9ed6","author":"anon-ab6221f8","content":"Fix forecast-bio/crosslink#655: git worktree add --orphan requires Git >=2.42.0; fails on Ubuntu 22.04's 2.34.1 with 'unknown option orphan'. Two production call sites: sync/cache.rs init_v3_host_worktree (crosslink/hub-v3-host) and knowledge/sync.rs init_cache (crosslink/knowledge). Added src/git_compat.rs with cached git-version detection (parse git --version, gate at 2.42) + add_orphan_worktree() that uses --orphan on new git and a fallback on old git: 'worktree add --detach' then 'checkout --orphan' then 'rm -rf .' to clear the tree, producing the identical unborn-orphan-empty-tree state. CROSSLINK_FORCE_WORKTREE_ORPHAN_FALLBACK env forces the fallback for testing. Both call sites rewired. Tests: version parse, gate boundary, fallback-equivalence (asserts unborn HEAD + empty index + root first commit); 320 sync+knowledge tests pass with the fallback FORCED end-to-end. clippy+fmt clean.","created_at":"2026-06-22T18:36:53.316093141Z","kind":"plan"}}
