{"agent_id":"anon-ab6221f8","agent_seq":12,"timestamp":"2026-06-22T19:00:04.227638091Z","event":{"type":"CommentAdded","issue_uuid":"4458c5a4-3ea7-45d5-9019-696ffc596bfc","comment_uuid":"d13da9a5-2361-4239-86d8-4a1cfaaf5a7e","author":"anon-ab6221f8","content":"Investigation: cannot reproduce the reported crash on current develop (identical to beta commit 7854152b for src/server/*). Faithfully reproduced the reporter's setup: built the real Vite frontend (produces the EXACT asset index-COsZ_-s7.js, 621KB + index-CZch84yR.css), rebuilt a RELEASE binary so rust-embed embeds it, and tested BOTH serving modes:\n- embedded (cargo install path): GET / =200, GET /assets/index-COsZ_-s7.js =200 (full 621851 bytes), CSS =200 — process ALIVE.\n- --dashboard-dir (ServeDir): same, all 200, process ALIVE.\nAlso probed CORS Origin, OPTIONS preflight, Range, missing asset, path traversal — all handled, no crash, in debug AND release.\nCode analysis: serve_embedded is panic-safe (header() stores error, body().unwrap_or_else catches it; mime_guess yields valid ASCII). No panic=abort in any profile, no process::exit/abort, no unsafe, no panic hook in the request path. Under panic=unwind a per-connection handler panic returns 500 and cannot kill the process. The only process-killers (stack overflow / abort) have no path here for a static GET.\nConclusion: not a reproducible code defect in the static-serving path on current code. Likely environment-specific (their Linux build/runtime) or browser-triggered WS/PTY, or a stale binary. Need the reporter's RUST_BACKTRACE output + exit signal (dmesg for SIGSEGV/OOM) to localize.","created_at":"2026-06-22T19:00:04.227631730Z","kind":"observation"}}
